{"id":8217,"date":"2023-12-29T12:03:16","date_gmt":"2023-12-29T12:03:16","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/?p=8217"},"modified":"2023-12-29T12:03:17","modified_gmt":"2023-12-29T12:03:17","slug":"how-to-prove-medical-negligence","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/how-to-prove-medical-negligence\/","title":{"rendered":"How to Prove Medical Negligence?"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" data-id=\"8218\" src=\"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/pexels-karolina-grabowska-71953691-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8218\" srcset=\"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/pexels-karolina-grabowska-71953691-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/pexels-karolina-grabowska-71953691-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/pexels-karolina-grabowska-71953691-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/pexels-karolina-grabowska-71953691.jpg 1279w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<span class=\"gdlr-core-space-shortcode\" style=\"margin-top: 30px ;\"  ><\/span>\n\n\n\n<p>When pursuing a medical negligence claim, it is crucial to <strong>gather the necessary evidence<\/strong> to support your case. This usually involves attending appointments with the relevant medical professionals and obtaining your medical records. In addition to this, <strong>you&#8217;ll need to prove breach of duty<\/strong>, which can be done by<a href=\"https:\/\/awhsolicitors.co.uk\/articles\/medical-negligence\/how-to-prove-medical-negligence\/\"> <\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/awhsolicitors.co.uk\/articles\/medical-negligence\/how-to-prove-medical-negligence\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">reviewing medical records and seeking an independent medical expert&#8217;s opinion<\/mark><\/a><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">.<\/mark><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Medical negligence can be a daunting and complex subject, but understanding how to prove it is essential if you believe you or a loved one has suffered at the hands of a healthcare professional. In simple terms, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.slatergordon.co.uk\/newsroom\/how-to-prove-medical-negligence\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">medical negligence<\/mark><\/a> occurs when a healthcare professional fails to meet the standard of care that a patient would reasonably expect, resulting in harm or injury.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is highly recommended to seek<a href=\"https:\/\/resolution.nhs.uk\/services\/claims-management\/advice-for-claimants\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\"> legal advice<\/mark><\/a> when dealing with medical negligence claims, as they can guide you through the process and help you gather the necessary evidence to maximise your chances of obtaining compensation. Remember, it is your right to seek recompense if you have suffered due to someone else&#8217;s negligence, and having the right support will help you achieve the best possible outcome.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Establishing Medical Negligence<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Understanding Duty of Care<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In the context of medical negligence, duty of care refers to the legal obligation that medical professionals have to provide a reasonable standard of care to their patients. As a patient, you are entitled to receive appropriate treatment, clear communication, and informed consent regarding your healthcare options.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Identifying Breach of Duty<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To establish a breach of duty, you must demonstrate that the healthcare provider failed to meet the required standard of care. Examples of breaches may include misdiagnosis, incorrect treatment, or failure to properly monitor a patient&#8217;s condition. Keep in mind that a poor outcome on its own does not necessarily signify negligence. Instead, consider whether a competent medical professional would have made the same decision under similar circumstances.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Proving Causation and Harm<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another key aspect of a medical negligence claim is proving that the breach of duty directly caused your injury or illness. This means establishing a clear link between the healthcare provider&#8217;s actions or omissions and the harm you suffered. Sometimes, this can be straightforward, such as when a surgical error leads to an obvious injury. However, proving causation can be more complex when the link between the breach and the harm is less clear.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Collecting Medical Evidence<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Gathering sufficient medical evidence is vital to support your claim. Start by obtaining copies of your<a href=\"https:\/\/www.slatergordon.co.uk\/newsroom\/how-to-prove-medical-negligence\/\"> <\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/www.slatergordon.co.uk\/newsroom\/how-to-prove-medical-negligence\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">medical records<\/mark><\/a>, which will document the appointments and treatments you received. Engaging an<a href=\"https:\/\/www.medicalnegligencelaw.org.uk\/prove-medical-negligence-in-the-uk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"> <mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">independent medical expert<\/mark><\/a> to review your case is also essential, as their testimony can help establish the appropriate standard of care and whether that standard was breached. Additionally, provide evidence of any financial losses you incurred, such as payslips or tax returns, if you are claiming for loss of earnings due to the negligence.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you pursue a medical negligence claim, remember that the process can be complex and challenging. Nonetheless, with the right evidence, legal expertise, and determination, you can hold the responsible parties accountable for any harm you suffered.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Pursuing a Medical Negligence Claim<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Timeline and Legal Process<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;re considering pursuing a medical negligence claim, it&#8217;s important to be aware of the timeline and legal process. Typically, you must issue your claim at court within three years of the alleged negligence taking place or within three years of becoming aware that something went wrong. However, individuals who lack &#8216;capacity&#8217; (under 18 years of age or without the mental ability to make necessary decisions) are not subject to a limitation period.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Choosing the Right Solicitor<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Selecting the<a href=\"https:\/\/awhsolicitors.co.uk\/articles\/medical-negligence\/how-to-prove-medical-negligence\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\"> right solicitor<\/mark><\/a> is crucial for a successful claim. Look for a solicitor with expertise in the area of medical negligence and discuss the details of your claim. A knowledgeable solicitor will help you gather evidence, understand the legal process and navigate the court system.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Potential Outcomes and Compensation<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In a medical negligence claim, compensation is typically divided into two categories:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>General damages<\/strong>: These compensate you for the pain, suffering and loss of amenity caused by the negligent medical treatment.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Special damages<\/strong>: These cover any financial losses and out-of-pocket expenses incurred due to the negligence. Examples include loss of earnings, medical expenses and travel costs.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>A successful claim will result in a<a href=\"https:\/\/awhsolicitors.co.uk\/articles\/medical-negligence\/how-to-prove-medical-negligence\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\"> compensation settlement<\/mark><\/a> that considers both general and special damages. The final amount will depend on the specifics of your case and the extent of your injuries.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Understanding No Win No Fee Agreements<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A common approach to funding a medical negligence claim is a &#8216;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.slatergordon.co.uk\/personal-injury-solicitors\/no-win-no-fee\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">No Win No Fee<\/mark><\/a>&#8216; agreement. This means that if your claim is unsuccessful, you won&#8217;t be required to pay any legal fees. However, if you win, your solicitor will receive a success fee from your compensation award. It&#8217;s essential to discuss all details of the agreement and the potential costs with your solicitor before proceeding.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>By being aware of the legal process, choosing the right solicitor, understanding the potential outcomes and compensation, and considering the financial arrangements, you can increase your chances of achieving the best possible result in your medical negligence claim.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Book a <a href=\"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/contact-us\/\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">free consultation<\/mark><\/a> now to speak to SG Murphy Solicitors, a <a href=\"https:\/\/murphysolicitors.co.uk\/medical-negligence-solicitors\/\" title=\"\"><mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">medical negligence solicitors <\/mark><\/a> who can guide you as to what your case is worth, taking in to account the specific circumstances of your case.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<span class=\"gdlr-core-space-shortcode\" style=\"margin-top: 30px ;\"  ><\/span>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>When pursuing a medical negligence claim, it is crucial to gather the necessary evidence to support your case. This usually involves attending appointments with the relevant medical professionals and obtaining your medical records. In addition to this, you&#8217;ll need to prove breach of duty, which can be done by reviewing medical records and seeking an [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8218,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_monsterinsights_sitenote_category":0,"footnotes":""},"categories":[2,3],"tags":[43],"class_list":["post-8217","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-p